                    <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-pr-en field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Strong Criticism against State Government for discontinuation of Madhavdeb Award<br />
“5 glaring instances of apathy towards tea labourers of Assam” Bhupen Bora</p>

<p>Guwahati, 4th September’23: APCC President, Mr. Bhupen Bora interacted with media today at Dibrugarh and strongly criticised the State Government for discontinuation of the Madhavdeb Award which was started during the Congress Congernment as a respect to the famous Vaishnavite saint of Assam.</p>

<p>Mr. Bora, who is continuously visiting the tea gardens of Assam and already covered 32 tea estates in last 8 days. Based on his interaction with tea laborers, Mr. Bora raised various pertinent issues faced by the tea labourers and challenged the CM of Assam to accompany him for a day to have first hand experience of the plight of the tea labourers in Assam. Mr. Bhupen Bora provided 5 instances of issues faced by the tea labourers including disfunctional Ujawala Scheme, the pathetic road condition, extremely high electricity bill etc. APCC President, Mr. Bora summarized that Congress party always stands by the cause of the tea labourers while the main interest of the BJP Government is only to sell existing tea estates or to buy resort. Finally, Mr. Bhupan Bora mentioned that after the completion of the “Bagane Bagane Program” of APCC, he will provide a list of 500 burning issues in the tea gardens of Assam and which impacting the tea labourers.</p>

<p><strong>Media Department, APCC</strong></p>
</div>
